&lt;p&gt;This is Jack Davis from Hangzhou, and I am now working on development of web front. We are GTUG Hangzhou China. （&lt;a href="http://groups.google.com/group/hangzhou-gtug"&gt;Hangzhou GTUG&lt;/a&gt;）&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We held the GTUG kick-off in Pingfeng Campus Zhejiang Industrial University in Nov 22, 2009 with Bill, Marketing manager Google China as special guest and other guests from all sectors of IT. Steve Zhi from Shanghai shared the experience on Python, Bill demonstrated products such as  Google Maps,O3D and Chrome OS. What is really exciting is our GTUG user TualatriX successfully demoed his own system built on Chrome OS and here is the &lt;a href="http://hangzhou-gtug.googlegroups.com/web/HZ_GTUG_Overview_1st_Event_Photos.pdf?gda=q92LuVgAAACoZAWfNpGZYd92s9pAYC3r7Xg80ufYQZOKQGlqLLHSDa7-6jIHtzrYc_Xc_5iCIRFFJ_j9kOZsu_E5C45lHxlZpsMJpo2PJSxJJuRrHXFqXxo1YHcDYvgcK1MwRk9oTs4"&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GTUG Hangzhou aims at helping IT people to learn and communicate about the latest Internet development tools, Google products, open web and open source technology as well as start up based on these technologies.We will co-operate with Google and other local partners in business ,media and academy to hold events and provide more opportunities for our members to discuss and share Google technologies and potential start-ups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The theme of GTUG is "Free, Creative, Dream". GTUG Hangzhou welcomes all friends domestic and abroad to discuss the development of technologies and improve ourselves together!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;
